      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;15.05 Baby Deer, Baby Boar, Baby Bear&amp;nbsp;(1)&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-04-a-big-cat/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;sup&gt;T/N: AKA Fawn, boarlet and cub, yes I know. I wanted to preserve some sort of metre considering this is a song and the &amp;#8216;baby&amp;#8217; does keep the theme running&amp;#8230; Feel free to suggest something that flows better. Poetry isn&amp;#8217;t my strong suit.&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-center wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&amp;#8220;&lt;em&gt;Baby deer, baby deer&lt;/em&gt;; &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Little baby deer.&lt;/em&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Eat lots of grass, lots of nuts and berries;&lt;/em&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;And when you grow big, run far, far away.&lt;/em&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Baby deer, baby deer&lt;/em&gt;; &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Little baby deer.&lt;/em&gt;&amp;#8220;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Tianyu was singing while plucking leaves from the stems. The leaves will be used for medicine.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œThat song, what is it?â€ Maomao asked him as she rolled her shoulders.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ahh, my body feels stiff.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;While reflecting that it could have been due to her lying in a strange posture, she had a stem in her hand. Tearing the leaves off individually was a hassle, so she stripped the leaves in one go by running her fingers down the stem. As the thick stems had thorns, she had to double-check before she did so.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Tianyu should be doing the same, but instead, he was tediously picking the leaves off one by one.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œHm? This song? Itâ€™s a nursery rhyme, nothing special,â€ he answered.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œHuh.â€ She didnâ€™t ask out of any particular great interest. It just had an oddly good rhythm to it that made her askâ€“donâ€™t get her wrong.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œWanna hear the second verse?â€&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œNot really.â€&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œUmm, the next verse isâ€¦â€&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-center wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&amp;#8220;&lt;em&gt;Baby boar, baby boar&lt;/em&gt;; &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Little baby boar&lt;/em&gt;. &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Eat lots of bugs, lots of bamboo shoots;&lt;/em&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;And when you grow big, run far, far away.&lt;/em&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Baby boar, baby boar&lt;/em&gt;; &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Little baby boar.&lt;/em&gt;&amp;#8220;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;So baby boar came after baby deer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œDeer and boar?â€ she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œYeah, I come from a family of hunters, you see. These guys are really adorable when theyâ€™re tiny, but once theyâ€™re adults, theyâ€™re hateful and troublesome, so everyone says. Weâ€™re delighted, thanks to that,â€ he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Deer and boar were pests, but at the same time, meat. The hunters must welcome them.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œWh