 had the same bewildered look as Changsha, while others were pale-faced like Yao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The former must be first-timers to dissections, while the latter had probably been told to take supplementary lessons.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao looked at Yao. â€œYao-san, you donâ€™t need to force yourself to participate.â€&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œIâ€™m not forcing myself,â€ Yao muttered. â€œItâ€™ll be fine, itâ€™ll be &lt;em&gt;fine&lt;/em&gt;.â€ It sounded like she was reassuring herself.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao let out a heavy breath. The air that came out was white and immediately dispersed. The base of her throat was cold, so she wrapped a towel around it. She took a set of blades out from her belongings.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œTake these,â€ Maomao handed the blades to Changsha. They were a set of three knives of differing length and widthâ€”something less fragile than surgical scalpels. â€œThese three knives are all you will be supplied with. If you need more, please purchase them yourself.â€&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao looked at Yao. The latter had a box with more than ten small blades with her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;It would be better if you finish with just these three, though.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Surgery wasnâ€™t like cooking. There was no time to select a tool during an emergency.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Enâ€™en was probably the one who assembled the tools, not Yao. It was clear that the tools were an attempt to compensate for Yao&amp;#8217;s lack of aptitude.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œWhat could today be?â€ Maomao headed over to the hunterâ€™s cabin, which she visited many times.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œWHOA,â€ Changsha screame