      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;SS: Sazen&amp;#8217;s Secret&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The sound of something falling on snow. Was it a dead body?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The man had stolen a horse from the stables and was fastening his loot to it. He had taken part in the Shi clan&amp;#8217;s insurrection. Of course, it wasnâ€™t out of some lofty ambition. The man was a peasantâ€“he only worked as a guard at the fortress to earn money for food.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;He was going to mount the horse and escape as soon as he could. What was he thinking, going to check to see what had fallen?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œ&amp;#8230;My lady?â€&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The girl was buried in the soft snow. Unconscious. There was a hole in the chest area of her dress. The unending white snow piled over her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Her name was Loulan. The daughter of the patriarch of the Shi clan, the leader of this insurrection. She had entered the inner palace to be the emperorâ€™s concubine.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Was she dead? No, puffs of her breath coloured the air white.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The man swallowed. The girl who had been summoned away by the person above the heavens was so dazzlingly beautiful to a peasant. Such a person was breathing weakly before his eyes.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œ&amp;#8230;Ngh.â€&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;A pained sound slipped out. She seemed to be really weak.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œFind her!&lt;em&gt; Find her&lt;/em&gt;!â€&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;He heard voices. It was the lot who came to suppress the insurrection.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The man panicked. If he didnâ€™t hightail it out of here in time, he may well be decapitated. And yet, the fallen girl weighed on his mind. She would be discovered if he left her be. Even if she werenâ€™t found, she would be buried in snow and freeze to death.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The man clutched his head, groaned and then sighed. He hoisted the girl out of the snow and over his shoulder.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œSorry. Itâ€™s a little heavy, so bear with it.â€&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The man offloaded one of the items he stole. There was another thing he had, but he couldnâ€™t get rid of those. He got on the horse with the girl in front of him and tugged the reins.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The man regretted picking up the unexpected thing he found. In an empty hut, he opened her dress. He couldnâ€™t leave her in wet clothes.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The hut was for hunters before they entered the forest. Thanks to that, there was a pelt, which he could use to cover and warm her up.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The girlâ€™s, Loulanâ€™s, chest was bruised blue-black. The hole in her dress was from a firearm. Be it luck, a silver hairstick had caught it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;With hesitation, the man extended his hand to Loulanâ€™s chest. While somehow keeping calm from the soft sensation, he checked the condition of her bones. Her ribs werenâ€™t broken. However, she had a fever and looked like she was in pain. She had fallen in the snow. Since her physical energy had dropped, it wouldnâ€™t be out of the ordinary for her to catch a cold.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;He wouldnâ€™t be able to run far with a sick person in tow. He would be quickly found if he brought Loulan with him. Loulan was certainly the daughter of his former employer, but he didnâ€™t have that much of a sense of duty to go that far. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Rather, he thought that having brought her to a hut where she wouldnâ€™t be discovered was good enough.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It was snowing outside. The snow probably wonâ€™t be stopping any time soon, but as he was used to long winters, he would have no trouble escaping in this environment by himself.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œ&amp;#8230;Can you, do me a favour?â€&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The man heard a hoarse voice. He turned around. Loulan, wrapped in the pelt, was awake.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œTh-these booksâ€¦â€&amp;nbsp; In Loulanâ€™s hand was an item the man had looted.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The cloth bag was filled with thick books. When did she see them?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œBring themâ€¦ to the capital.â€&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œ&amp;#8230;What are you saying?â€ he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It was troubling that she was telling him to take them to the capital. The man was currently on the run because of the army that came from the very capital. Once it was known that he participated in the insurrection, he would be arrested.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;â€œI beg, of youâ€¦â€ She got up and bowed her head deeply. The woman who had slept with the emperor before was doing that.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt